			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Most likely, your IP internet address is changed in between: for some reason, the internet provider re-connect your computer and gave a new IP, highly different to the old one. In this case, ATC decides you are a new user and asks a question.
<br />

<br />
There is no way to avoid IP-check because it's the important part of anti-spam protection. It shouldn't be possible that spammers get a pass-code once and than spam from theirs botnets.<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
